red the starting point for the emergence of NFT.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"> </span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">ERC-20 is simply the standard by which most interchangeable tokens are created. The best way to look at \"interchangeability\" is with fiat money. If you and I each have a $10 bill and we exchange it we will each have $10 because both of those bills were issued with the expectation that they are identical and equivalent to each other for making payments. If I have a ticket for the Eminem concert and you have a ticket for the Barcelona-Real Madrid match and we exchange them as well, no big deal (at least for me because I\'m a soccer fan). However, these tickets will not be equivocal for the respective events, but they will also differ in their value if we want to sell them.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"> </span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">The irrevocability of an item arises because of its properties, and the same is true for tokens.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"> </span></span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 18pt;\"><strong>In-game NFTs on Jollity</strong></span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">On our platform, we use Non-Fungible Tokens technology to ensure that every gamer can permanently secure the ownership of their in-game items in blockchain and store them in their wallet. Owning in-game NFTs not only enables you to securely buy, sell, exchange, or rent these items, but it also gives you full control over the items, not the game developers or our platform.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"> </span></span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">NFT has already had a huge impact on the popularization of decentralized technology in the gaming industry, following the release of games like Axie infinity, Sorare, or Star Atlas and we are going to do our part to see how the gaming industry will change for good very soon after the arrival of blockchain.</span>', 'WTF are NFTs?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '171-revision-v1', '', '', '2022-01-14 05:25:06', '2022-01-14 02:25:06', '', 171, 'https://jollity.app/blog/?p=179', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
