(211, 1, '2022-01-14 21:07:54', '2022-01-14 18:07:54', '<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">An NFT token is a unique digital certificate stored in a blockchain that secures exclusive rights to the owner of a certain item. For many people, this magic abbreviation is already familiar but since we want our users to be as involved in Jollity products as we are, we need to give a simple and clear definition for the technology around which we are building our project.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"> </span></span>\n\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">To better understand the nature of non-fungible tokens, let\'s take a brief excursion to the origins of the technology.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"> </span></span>\n\n<span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Where was the beginning</strong></span>\n\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Bitcoin made popular the cryptocurrency industry and exposed millions of people to blockchain technology showing that decentralized stores of information can work well in the financial industry. Blockchain which is a distributed ledger allows any data to be stored securely and transparently. The concept of distributed data allowed the creation of Bitcoin which stored in a blockchain data on all transactions made but had limited functionality so the logical development in the field of cryptocurrencies was Ethereum and its blockchain created by Vitalik Buterin which uses blockchains to decentralize much more complex information, including scripts. Developers began to use Ethereum to create new cryptocurrencies (often called tokens) with a wide variety of functionality. Subsequently, standards for tokens emerged because it was necessary to encode more complex data structures as well as to combine one software with others. The creation of these standards can be considered the starting point for the emergence of NFT.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"> </span></span>\n\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">ERC-20 is simply the standard by which most interchangeable tokens are created. The best way to look at \"interchangeability\" is with fiat money. If you and I each have a $10 bill and we exchange it we will each have $10 because both of those bills were issued with the expectation that they are identical and equivalent to each other for making payments. If I have a ticket for the Eminem concert and you have a ticket for the Barcelona-Real Madrid match and we exchange them as well, no big deal (at least for me because I\'m a football fan). However, these tickets will not be equivocal for the respective events, but they will also differ in their value if we want to sell them.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"> </span></span>\n\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">The irrevocability of an item arises because of its properties, and the same is true for tokens.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"> </span></span>\n\n<span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>In-game NFTs on Jollity</strong></span>\n\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">On our platform, we use non-interchangeable tokens technology to ensure that every gamer can permanently secure the ownership of their in-game items in blockchain and store them in their wallet. Owning in-game NFTs not only enables you to securely buy, sell, exchange, or rent these items, but it also gives you full control over the items, not the game developers or our platform.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"> </span></span>\n\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">NFT has already had a huge impact on the popularization of decentralized technology in the gaming industry, following the release of games like Axie infinity, Sorare, or Star Atlas and we are going to do our part to see how the gaming industry will change for good very soon after the arrival of blockchain.</span>\n\n&nbsp;', 'What are NFTs?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '170-revision-v1', '', '', '2022-01-14 21:07:54', '2022-01-14 18:07:54', '', 170, 'https://jollity.app/blog/?p=211', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
